@jaspermdegroot Thanks for the helpful code and steps to reproduce. I've found the problem. It's actually a known issue (<a class="new ticket" href="http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/24844" title="#24844: defect (bug): get_theme_mods doesn't return the theme customizer preview's new values. (new)">#24844</a>) where <code>get_theme_mods()</code> isn't returning the customizer-previewed values. The fix is simply to use <code>get_theme_mod()</code> instead. I've implemented this and fixed an issue with the content alignment sanitize callback here: <a class="ext-link" href="https://gist.github.com/westonruter/c9b9cf597e9e9129070d67b68920168e/revisions"><span class="icon">​</span>https://gist.github.com/westonruter/c9b9cf597e9e9129070d67b68920168e/revisions</a>
</p>
